radiographic_examinations.findings: The sella turcica and the hypophysis were not identifiable; ectopic or undescended neurohypophysis present near the tuber cinereum.
Absent sella turcica and anterior pituitary gland; potential neurohypophyseal tissue detected close to the tuber cinereum.
Partial agenesis of the corpus callosum, small anterior pituitary gland, and optic chiasm; dysplasia of the cerebellar vermis.
